Subject: Parking brake

Sounds like to me you had a heavy load which squatted the truck. It adjusted
your cable when you trailing arm moved.  Which of course shouldn't happen.
Check to see if both ends at the body to the brake baking plate are seated.
You may be in need of new cables.

Richard Jack
